Reviews.Title: installed easily
Reviews.Author: R. J Sepeta "Procrastination is the thief of ...
Reviews.Content: it worked ok but i felt that the cable quality could have been a little better. i was hoping for it to be more stiff, and easier to pull through the ceiling tiles.

Reviews.Title: Good construction, not even terminated correctly...
Reviews.Author: Brett
Reviews.Content: I received the wire, looked like a good product.  Came in a thick plastic bag, I removed the product, the rubber shielding around the wire was nice and thick, better than most bag/box pre-terminated wire out there.  I hooked it up to a camera I had for testing, it never even powered on.  Checked things out, turns out the BNC portion of the cable wasn't even touching the inside termination.  Once I cut the head off and re-terminated , worked fine.*sigh*

Reviews.Title: Won't Fit
Reviews.Author: Michael Gardner
Reviews.Content: The bnc connectors must be from Mars.  They do not fit any connections.  It seems like the pin connector in the center of the bnc is of a too large diameter.  The cable seems very good as does the power connector.  It is a shame that there is this problem since the product looks good.  Amazon is getting an RMA.

Reviews.Title: Horrible cables
Reviews.Author: TOM
Reviews.Content: This 25 feet cable is extremely thin and cheap. I bought 3 of these extensions to work with the Q-See High Resolution Weatherproof CCD Camera. The cables are very thin, slightly thicker then a toothpick. This horrible cable carries very blurry video image and lost signalThis horrible cable carry very blurry and flucky video image and lost signal.

Reviews.Title: Good cable
Reviews.Author: Mr. Isotope
Reviews.Content: I needed a 25' cable, and so went with this one.  The cable seems to be good quality and not super-thin like some cheap cables that I have used in the past.  It arrived USPS priority mail and came very quickly.  I would definitely buy them again.
